			<ns0:name>erik...@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/104389777848534510881/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">From a customer report: (using newlib)

The c-library supplies information on locale, via the function 'locale'.. which can in theory return the current system locale setting (eg. american english), by creating a 'locale' object with the empty string (ie. locale(&amp;quot;&amp;quot;)). It seems however, that this function on NACL is hardwired to return the default locale of &amp;quot;C&amp;quot; always, instead of the current system setting (eg. &amp;quot;en-US&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;en-GB&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;fr&amp;quot; .. etc..) 
